{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails-girls-summer-of-code/rgsoc-teams/pulls/comments/116868595", "pull_request_review_id": 38502378, "id": 116868595, "diff_hunk": "@@ -7,6 +7,22 @@\n   it { is_expected.to have_many(:attendees) }\n   it { is_expected.to validate_presence_of(:name) }\n   it { is_expected.to validate_presence_of(:round) }\n+  it { is_expected.to validate_presence_of(:starts_on) }\n+  it { is_expected.to validate_presence_of(:ends_on) }\n+\n+  describe 'it checks the chronological order of dates' do", "path": "spec/models/conference_spec.rb", "position": null, "original_position": 7, "commit_id": "feaebc7d62b276885c233762297245bcc6542673", "original_commit_id": "0bf907889b555355ad180c5d8a6a5be9f5b50281", "user": {"login": "klappradla", "id": 3491815, "avatar_url": "https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/3491815?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/klappradla", "html_url": "https://github.com/klappradla", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/klappradla/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/klappradla/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/klappradla/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/klappradla/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/klappradla/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/klappradla/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/klappradla/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/klappradla/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/klappradla/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "Using `it` anywhere within a spec fine is kind of an *\"rspec smell\"* \ud83d\ude09 \r\n\r\nThe purpose of the `describe` block would be to group some examples. So here, this could for instance be:\r\n```ruby\r\ndescribe 'validate dates' do\r\n  # do stuff\r\n```", "created_at": "2017-05-16T21:57:42Z", "updated_at": "2017-05-19T14:23:45Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails-girls-summer-of-code/rgsoc-teams/pull/747#discussion_r116868595", "pull_request_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails-girls-summer-of-code/rgsoc-teams/pulls/747", "author_association": "MEMBER", "_links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails-girls-summer-of-code/rgsoc-teams/pulls/comments/116868595"}, "html": {"href": "https://github.com/rails-girls-summer-of-code/rgsoc-teams/pull/747#discussion_r116868595"}, "pull_request": {"href": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails-girls-summer-of-code/rgsoc-teams/pulls/747"}}, "body_html": "<p>Using <code>it</code> anywhere within a spec fine is kind of an <em>\"rspec smell\"</em> <g-emoji class=\"g-emoji\" alias=\"wink\" fallback-src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f609.png\">\ud83d\ude09</g-emoji></p>\n<p>The purpose of the <code>describe</code> block would be to group some examples. So here, this could for instance be:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-ruby\"><pre>describe <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span>validate dates<span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span></span> <span class=\"pl-k\">do</span>\n  <span class=\"pl-c\"><span class=\"pl-c\">#</span> do stuff</span></pre></div>", "body_text": "Using it anywhere within a spec fine is kind of an \"rspec smell\" \ud83d\ude09\nThe purpose of the describe block would be to group some examples. So here, this could for instance be:\ndescribe 'validate dates' do\n  # do stuff"}